<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              Foreground="#E0E0E0"
              Background="#1E1F22"
              FontFamily="Segoe UI"
              FontSize="14"
              PagePadding="32,24,32,24">

    <Paragraph FontSize="28" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Exporting PRM Objects
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#A0A0A0" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,0,16">
        How to save a completed PRM object for use in Urban Chaos or export it as OBJ for another editor.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,0,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- SAVE AS PRM -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,4,0,4">
        Saving as PRM
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Once the object has been modelled, textured, and configured, save it as a PRM file using
        <Bold>Save As PRM</Bold>. This opens a save dialog in the prim directory and allows you to
        choose the PRM file name or slot to overwrite.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosPrimEditor;component/Help/Images/prim_export_save_as_prm.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph>
        Urban Chaos loads prims by number. The engine checks
        <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">NPRIM</Run>
        entries first, and if no matching file is found there, it then checks
        <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">PRIM</Run>
        entries. This means the file name and slot number matter.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        At the moment, all 255 prim slots are considered occupied. If you are adding a custom object,
        you normally need to overwrite an existing slot. Refer to the project documentation or wiki
        for PRM objects that are not used or make good overwrite candidates.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#3A2A2A" BorderBrush="#7A4A4A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#E0A0A0">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Important:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Always keep backups of original PRM files before overwriting game files.
                    Once a slot is replaced, maps that reference that prim number may show your new object instead.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- EXPORT OBJ -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Exporting as OBJ
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        You can also export the current model as an
        <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">.OBJ</Run>
        file by selecting <Bold>Export OBJ</Bold>. This is useful if you want to continue editing the
        object in another 3D package or keep an interchange-format backup of the mesh.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        OBJ export is separate from game export. Saving as OBJ does not make the object available to
        the game. To use the object in Urban Chaos, it must still be saved as a PRM file in the
        correct prim directory and referenced by the appropriate prim number.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosPrimEditor;component/Help/Images/prim_export_obj.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- FINAL CHECKS -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Before Exporting
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Before saving a final PRM, check the following:
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>The texture directory is correct and all textures display properly.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Every face that should be visible has a texture assigned.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>UV regions are correct and are not accidentally using the wrong part of a texture.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Collision type, damage type, shadow type, and object flags are set appropriately.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>The object is low-poly enough for practical game use.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>The model stays below the approximate 5000-vertex engine limit.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>You have backed up the original PRM file if you are overwriting an existing slot.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Recommended Export Workflow
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set the texture directory.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set the game prim directory.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create, import, or load the model.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Edit geometry and confirm the face structure.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Texture every required face and adjust UV regions.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Configure collision, damage, shadow, and special flags.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Save as PRM to the intended prim slot.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Optionally export OBJ as a backup or for further editing.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

</FlowDocument>
